description:
&lt;p&gt;We are very excited to recruit a full time Support Worker to join our Community CAMHS service. You will be part of our supportive multi-disciplinary team, and will be working in our Eating Disorder Clinic and our Neurodevelopmental Clinic as well as providing clinic based and community based support to children and young people who are suffering with mental health difficulties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are interested to hear from applicants who have Child and Adolescent Mental Health expertise and experience. We are a busy and dynamic CAMHS team where there are opportunities to enhance your existing skills and learn new ones as the Trust is supportive of CPD and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Carey Gurd, Clinical Team Manager or Lottie Mellor, Deputy Team Manager Tel: 01865 903422&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
